cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses the relationship between kernel-based quadrature rules and random feature expansions, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper deals with the analysis of approximation errors and the number of required samples. The paper also touches upon the topic of control systems (cs.SY) as it discusses the generalization guarantees for learning with Lipshitz-continuous losses. Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the problem of full function approximations.
